---
By: Amaury de Riencourt
Locus:
  Page: 244
  Verse: 4
Tags:
  - Heaven
---
Let us imagine a crossroads with one sign on the right pointing “to heaven”
and another on the left pointing to “lectures on heaven.” The Easterner
would turn right and go straight to heaven, when the Westerner would turn
left and attend the lectures.
